390
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:38,200
I just don't want these things to get covered by dust here.

391
00:23:38,350 --> 00:23:40,000
I'm just moving them to a new place.

392
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:40,720
Don't move.

393
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:42,440
Chao, come and take a look.

394
00:23:42,550 --> 00:23:43,480
I think we should find a cabinet

395
00:23:44,070 --> 00:23:45,960
to display these things.

396
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:47,920
What do you think?

397
00:23:50,030 --> 00:23:50,720
Okay.

398
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:52,070
Okay, I'll find a place.

399
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:53,830
I'll buy one for you tomorrow.

400
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:54,550
Okay.

401
00:23:56,070 --> 00:23:58,960
I've never seen so many trophies in my life.

402
00:23:58,960 --> 00:23:59,920
Take them back.

403
00:24:00,550 --> 00:24:01,720
They are not mine.

404
00:24:02,510 --> 00:24:03,960
There is no name on them anyway.

405
00:24:04,070 --> 00:24:04,790
Besides,

406
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:06,590
what belongs to me is also yours, right?

407
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:08,960
That makes sense.

408
00:24:08,960 --> 00:24:09,880
I'll take them then.

409
00:24:22,110 --> 00:24:22,790
Godmother.

410
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:23,830
Come here.

411
00:24:25,070 --> 00:24:25,750
Well.

412
00:24:26,270 --> 00:24:28,960
There is nothing on this wall.

413
00:24:29,160 --> 00:24:31,200
Shouldn't we put something on it?

414
00:24:33,030 --> 00:24:33,680
Son.

415
00:24:33,720 --> 00:24:34,590
You're tall.

416
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:36,000
Put it on the wall.

417
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:37,750
No.

418
00:24:41,960 --> 00:24:43,110
This picture was taken years ago.

419
00:24:44,160 --> 00:24:45,070
Let's take a new one.

420
00:24:45,550 --> 00:24:48,070
I'm relieved. Yes. Come on.

421
00:24:50,030 --> 00:24:51,720
Finally, we have a new family photo.

422
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:54,830
Okay.

423
00:24:55,750 --> 00:24:57,510
Sit up. Ling. Sit up.

424
00:24:59,240 --> 00:24:59,920
OK.

425
00:25:00,110 --> 00:25:02,310
Three, two.

426
00:25:02,310 --> 00:25:03,110
Wait. Wait.

427
00:25:03,110 --> 00:25:04,240
You too, Little Rabbit.

428
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:05,240
Yeah. Take a photo with us.

429
00:25:05,240 --> 00:25:05,830
Come on.

430
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:06,830
OK.

431
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:28,680
Where are you taking me?

432
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:29,590
Guess.

433
00:25:29,590 --> 00:25:31,240
You guess if I'll guess or not.

434
00:25:31,440 --> 00:25:32,510
I guess you won't.

435
00:25:32,960 --> 00:25:33,680
The snack shop.

436
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:35,920
What did you do here?

437
00:25:37,440 --> 00:25:38,160
What did you do?

438
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:39,240
What did I do?

439
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:42,960
I remember I snatched your little red flower here.

440
00:25:51,720 --> 00:25:54,350
I have a red flower. I have a red flower.

441
00:25:57,960 --> 00:25:59,270
Then you got carried away

442
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:00,790
and ran into the tree.

443
00:26:01,680 --> 00:26:04,070
And when I was having a competition with you,

444
00:26:04,160 --> 00:26:06,200
my new pants were broken.

445
00:26:08,750 --> 00:26:12,070
That was one of the most embarrassing occasions in my life.

446
00:26:12,790 --> 00:26:14,000
I think it was here.

447
00:26:21,070 --> 00:26:22,480
Oh no, my pants are broken.

448
00:26:22,480 --> 00:26:23,480
Ling Chao.

449
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:25,110
Are you okay?

450
00:26:25,270 --> 00:26:26,830
My pants are broken.

451
00:26:28,030 --> 00:26:30,310
And you got beaten up by your godmother after going home.

452
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:32,550
You insisted on playing this game.

453
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:34,750
You asked me to play it.

454
00:26:36,920 --> 00:26:39,640
You don't like meat, do you?

455
00:26:41,030 --> 00:26:42,200
Give it to me.

456
00:26:42,790 --> 00:26:43,920
Give it to me.

457
00:26:53,510 --> 00:26:54,790
You're the best.

458
00:26:57,400 --> 00:26:59,720
Do you need me to help you recall what happened?

459
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:01,310
No.

460
00:27:01,550 --> 00:27:03,070
I remember it clearly.

461
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:05,400
After that, every time I had oden,

462
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:07,880
I kept the stick in my hand.

463
00:27:08,640 --> 00:27:09,750
Have you noticed that

464
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:12,110
every time you pick on me,

465
00:27:12,750 --> 00:27:13,960
you are the one to suffer in the end?

466
00:27:15,440 --> 00:27:17,030
I help you clean up the mess.

467
00:27:17,790 --> 00:27:18,680
Right.

468
00:27:24,550 --> 00:27:25,480
Do you like this place?

469
00:27:26,270 --> 00:27:27,310
Yes.

470
00:27:29,510 --> 00:27:31,960
Mu Yehan proposed under a sky wheel.

471
00:27:32,790 --> 00:27:34,480
So I guess you'll like it.

472
00:27:34,960 --> 00:27:35,640
Who?

473
00:27:37,110 --> 00:27:38,030
Mu Yehan.

474
00:27:38,960 --> 00:27:40,960
The book you read in high school.

475
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:42,440
The cover is in English.

476
00:27:42,550 --> 00:27:43,240
But it was

477
00:27:43,240 --> 00:27:45,000
actually a romance novel.

478
00:27:46,110 --> 00:27:48,240
You read it?

479
00:27:52,110 --> 00:27:53,960
So you should know

480
00:27:54,240 --> 00:27:55,440
what I want to tell you today.

481
00:28:04,350 --> 00:28:06,240
Before your college entrance exam scores were announced,

482
00:28:08,680 --> 00:28:10,240
I thought

483
00:28:11,030 --> 00:28:13,510
if we couldn't go to the same university,

484
00:28:14,920 --> 00:28:16,480
and if you didn't come to Yunhai,

485
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:18,590
would we go our separate ways

486
00:28:18,590 --> 00:28:20,680
like other childhood sweethearts

487
00:28:21,720 --> 00:28:22,750
just like that?

488
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:25,920
But then I thought about it.

489
00:28:29,480 --> 00:28:30,270
We won't.

490
00:28:32,310 --> 00:28:33,830
Are you that confident?

491
00:28:40,680 --> 00:28:42,590
If we were always together,

492
00:28:43,480 --> 00:28:45,550
I might never have this feeling.

493
00:28:47,160 --> 00:28:48,440
But we separated

494
00:28:50,240 --> 00:28:51,480
in the first year of college.

495
00:28:53,750 --> 00:28:55,920
I walked a long road alone.

496
00:28:59,270 --> 00:29:01,400
But I still wanted to come back to you.

497
00:29:01,680 --> 00:29:02,640
I'm not home.

498
00:29:02,750 --> 00:29:04,510
I don't know if she can handle it herself.

499
00:29:06,640 --> 00:29:09,200
So I'm more confident in you

500
00:29:12,960 --> 00:29:14,400
than in myself.

501
00:29:16,750 --> 00:29:17,750
I made a bet.

502
00:29:18,480 --> 00:29:20,160
No matter where we go,

503
00:29:22,830 --> 00:29:24,400
I still want to go back to the stairway in the childhood

504
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:25,640
to wait for you.

505
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:35,880
As long as I wait,

506
00:29:38,790 --> 00:29:39,830
you will come.

507
00:29:42,440 --> 00:29:44,640
Congratulations.

508
00:29:45,440 --> 00:29:46,550
You win.

509
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:53,480
We may

510
00:29:56,440 --> 00:29:58,680
see different scenery in life.

511
00:30:00,200 --> 00:30:01,680
But only when I'm with you,

512
00:30:01,680 --> 00:30:02,830
I'm not just passing by.

513
00:30:07,270 --> 00:30:08,720
It's called the eternity of a moment.

514
00:30:14,110 --> 00:30:15,750
So, will you marry me

515
00:30:19,070 --> 00:30:21,030
and enjoy more scenery with me?

516
00:30:21,920 --> 00:30:22,750
Yes.

517
00:30:26,400 --> 00:30:29,030
Shouldn't you have a ring when you propose?

518
00:30:29,070 --> 00:30:30,440
Where is your ring?

519
00:30:32,790 --> 00:30:34,550
I came out in a hurry.

520
00:30:34,960 --> 00:30:36,000
I didn't have time to prepare.

521
00:30:36,590 --> 00:30:37,790
So I'll give you the ring later.

522
00:30:38,960 --> 00:30:40,270
No.

523
00:30:55,640 --> 00:30:56,270
What do you think?

524
00:30:56,880 --> 00:30:58,030
Are you satisfied

525
00:30:58,510 --> 00:30:59,480
with my new magic?

526
00:31:00,070 --> 00:31:04,000
Are you going to write a program next?

527
00:31:07,790 --> 00:31:10,960
I wanted to write a program

528
00:31:11,790 --> 00:31:13,720
to propose to you

529
00:31:13,720 --> 00:31:14,830
at the top of the sky wheel.

530
00:31:15,440 --> 00:31:16,270
If you don't agree,

531
00:31:17,510 --> 00:31:18,510
I won't let you come down.

532
00:31:19,240 --> 00:31:20,550
How dare you!

533
00:31:21,590 --> 00:31:22,830
But I thought about it.

534
00:31:25,070 --> 00:31:26,200
You'll definitely say yes.

535
00:31:26,920 --> 00:31:27,830
So I gave up the plan.

536
00:31:29,310 --> 00:31:30,400
Come on.

537
00:31:30,400 --> 00:31:32,200
You just don't want to buy tickets.

538
00:31:32,350 --> 00:31:33,070
Yes.

539
00:31:34,270 --> 00:31:35,070
Alright.

540
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:37,240
Let me tell you a secret.

541
00:32:10,590 --> 00:32:11,240
I love you.

542
00:32:20,270 --> 00:32:21,720
I love you more.

543
00:32:22,920 --> 00:32:23,750
How much do you love me?

544
00:32:25,550 --> 00:32:28,830
I'll give you

545
00:32:28,960 --> 00:32:30,680
everything good.

546
00:32:37,240 --> 00:32:38,720
It's so beautiful.

547
00:32:40,110 --> 00:32:40,750
Look.

548
00:32:41,240 --> 00:32:42,000
Is it beautiful?

549
00:32:42,550 --> 00:32:43,160
Dad.

550
00:32:43,160 --> 00:32:43,960
Look.

551
00:32:44,030 --> 00:32:45,000
There are fireworks.

552
00:33:30,480 --> 00:33:33,400
My mom said when I was born,

553
00:33:33,590 --> 00:33:36,960
I was most welcomed by my dad.

554
00:33:37,590 --> 00:33:38,640
So cute.

555
00:33:40,400 --> 00:33:42,030
You're a man.

556
00:33:42,880 --> 00:33:44,640
Let me change your diaper.

557
00:33:46,030 --> 00:33:49,510
I heard that other children's parents

558
00:33:49,510 --> 00:33:52,030
never allow them to watch cartoons.

559
00:33:52,480 --> 00:33:54,270
But my dad is different.

560
00:33:54,920 --> 00:33:58,400
He let me watch as long as I want.

561
00:34:06,550 --> 00:34:07,350
Dad said

562
00:34:07,590 --> 00:34:10,710
men should eat more carrots if they want to be tall.

563
00:34:10,920 --> 00:34:13,230
I want to be as tall as Dad,

564
00:34:13,320 --> 00:34:15,110
so that I can protect my mom.

565
00:34:20,070 --> 00:34:21,670
Every weekend,

566
00:34:21,800 --> 00:34:23,960
my dad will send me

567
00:34:23,960 --> 00:34:27,440
to my grandparents.

568
00:34:27,590 --> 00:34:28,710
Because he said

569
00:34:29,230 --> 00:34:30,880
"be well-behaved and filial".

570
00:34:31,030 --> 00:34:33,960
Being filial is the most important thing in life.

571
00:34:34,320 --> 00:34:36,920
When I grow up, I'll be filial to my parents

572
00:34:37,190 --> 00:34:39,710
like this.

573
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:50,000
Wait.

574
00:34:50,030 --> 00:34:50,760
What's wrong?

575
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:53,840
I suddenly remember

576
00:34:54,190 --> 00:34:55,840
